When he will get a connection back, he will be able to synchronize its local database with the common centralized database.</td></tr><tr class="print"><td class="print-category">Steps To Reproduce</td><td class="print" colspan="5"></td></tr><tr class="print"><td class="print-category">Additional Information</td><td class="print" colspan="5">When designing this feature, a great care should be taken that the local database stored on the user's computer is encrypted and cannot be read.<br />
<br />
Using the &quot;delete Offline website data&quot; option in Firefox is enough to destroy the data stored on the user's computer. This solution has been considered sufficiently good by the final users. It should be thoroughly tested in the integration tests of the feature.<br />
<br />
